  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense. If caught, potential legal consequences can include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Potential prison sentences\n- Substantial financial penalties/fines\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Forfeit of laundered funds\n- Large monetary fines\n- Seizure of assets connected to crime\n\n3. Professional consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential business/professional disqualifications\n\n4. Civil penalties\n- Government can file civil lawsuits\n- Additional financial damages\n\n5. Specific potential outcomes\n- Felony conviction\n- 5-20 years imprisonment depending on circumstances\n- Fines up to $500,000 or double the property value involved\n\nActual consequences depend on specific circumstances, amount of money, jurisdiction, and individual case details.",
